> Tips: If we don't explicitly assign a type to a variable, then the compiler will infer one for us.

```rust,editable

// Remove something to make it work
fn main() {
    let x: i32 = 5;
    let mut y: u32 = 5;

    y = x;
    
    let z = 10; // Type of z ? 

    println!("Success!");
}
```
fn main() {
    let x: u32 = 5;
    let mut y: u32 = 5;

    y = x;

    let z = 10; 

    println!("Success!");
}

